<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-15649] test.distributed.timeout no longer respected in CircleCI</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15649</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After switching jvm dtest over testclasslist (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15508&quot; title=&quot;Failing jvm dtest: FailingRepairTest.testFailingMessage&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-15508&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-15508&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) we no longer respect the dtest timeout and instead use the unit test timeout (4m vs 6m).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This does not impact Jenkins as I made sure to check that before calling testclasslist; though this does impact 2.2, 3.0, and 3.11 as well.&lt;/p&gt;

