                            <comment id="17063859" author="michaelsembwever" created="Sat, 21 Mar 2020 11:04:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Quick question on why the uninstall of cqlsh is happening in this patch?&lt;br/&gt;
(And I can&apos;t access the CircleCI links&#8230;?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17064019" author="dcapwell" created="Sat, 21 Mar 2020 18:29:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sorry, talked to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=djoshi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;djoshi&quot;&gt;djoshi&lt;/a&gt; about that.  looks like when python3 was added LOWER and HIGHER were updated, but config.yml was not replaced with config.yml.LOWER (undocumented, something you have to do though).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since I changed the build, I had to update config.yml to pick that up (cp config.yml.LOWER config.yml)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;(And I can&apos;t access the CircleCI links&#8230;?)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;_&lt;/del&gt;  that isn&apos;t good... ill try to figure out why Monday.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17065784" author="michaelsembwever" created="Tue, 24 Mar 2020 13:51:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dcapwell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dcapwell&quot;&gt;dcapwell&lt;/a&gt;, could you provide the 2.2, 3.0, and 3.11 patches please. (as the trunk patch does not cleanly apply.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17066289" author="dcapwell" created="Wed, 25 Mar 2020 00:46:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mck&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mck&quot;&gt;mck&lt;/a&gt; sent for all 4. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17066832" author="dcapwell" created="Wed, 25 Mar 2020 16:37:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;in case the CI runs are not visible (reached out to circle ci team about this), all LOWERs passed and confirmed the change took affect (2.2 had a test failure, I don&apos;t monitor 2.2 so not familiar with its flaky tests, but I did see the change was picked up).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17067742" author="michaelsembwever" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2020 14:55:12 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;in case the CI runs are not visible (reached out to circle ci team about this), all LOWERs passed and confirmed the change took affect (2.2 had a test failure, I don&apos;t monitor 2.2 so not familiar with its flaky tests, but I did see the change was picked up).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks. (The circleci links are still not visible)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17067981" author="dcapwell" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2020 19:28:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;since Circle CI is locking down workflows for some reason, ill take a screen shot of the DAG + the params and attach to JIRA.  There are test failures, for trunk I linked to the flaky test JIRA, for other builds I don&apos;t have history so don&apos;t know what&apos;s flaky.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17068018" author="dcapwell" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2020 20:34:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the 2.2 builds spam stdout so the UI doesn&apos;t show the ant command, so print out the script.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
